data.enText: needing sb/sth in order to survive or be successful
a woman with several dependent children
data.chText: 一个女人带着几个未自立的孩子

data.enText: You can't be dependent on your parents all your life.
data.chText: 你不可能一辈子靠父母生活。

data.enText: The festival is heavily dependent on sponsorship for its success.
data.chText: 这次节日庆祝活动成功与否，在很大程度上就看赞助了。

data.enText: addicted to sth (= unable to stop taking or using it)
A child's development is dependent on many factors.
data.chText: 孩子的成长受多种因素影响。

data.enText: The price is dependent on how many extras you choose.
data.chText: 价格取决于你挑选额外收费项目的多少。

word_means: 被扶养人：被赡养人：非独立生活的人

means: 被扶养人：被赡养人：非独立生活的人

tr: a person who relies on another person for support (especially financial support)
relying on or requiring a person or thing for support, supply, or what is needed
(of a clause) unable to stand alone syntactically as a complete sentence
example: a subordinate (or dependent) clause functions as a noun or adjective or adverb within a sentence

tr: being under the power or sovereignty of another or others

example.ex: The local economy is overwhelmingly dependent on oil and gas extraction...
example.tran: 当地经济过于依赖石油和天然气的开采。

example.ex: Up to two million people there are dependent on food aid...
example.tran: 那里有多达 200 万人口依靠食品援助。

example.ex: Britain became increasingly dependent upon American technology...
example.tran: 英国变得越来越依赖美国的技术了。

example.ex: In his own way, he was dependent on her...
example.tran: 他以自己的方式依赖着她。

example.ex: Just 26 per cent of households are married couples with dependent children.
example.tran: 只有26%的家庭是有孩子要扶养的已婚夫妇。

value.def: To be dependent on something or someone means to need them in order to succeed or be able to survive.

example.ex: The results you get from weight training are largely dependent upon how you use those weights and what type of exercise programme you follow.
example.tran: 举重训练的效果在很大程度上取决于如何使用那些举重器械以及遵照何种锻炼方案。

example.ex: The treatment of infertility is largely dependent on the ability of couples to pay.
example.tran: 对不孕不育的治疗很大程度上视乎夫妇的经济能力。

value.def: If one thing is dependent on another, the first thing will be affected or determined by the second.
